                <h1>Understanding Gun Ownership Restrictions in Texas</h1>
                <p>In Texas, certain factors disqualify individuals from owning a gun. These include felony convictions, a history of domestic violence, restraining orders, mental health issues, substance abuse problems, or being a minor. It's crucial for potential gun owners to understand these restrictions to ensure compliance with state laws.</p>
